   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="description" n="monument">
            <head>Description of Monument</head>
            <p>Upper part of a simple <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> without moulding (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.52</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.455</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.42</measure>).</p>
         </div>
         <div type="description" n="text">
            <head>Description of Text</head>
            <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face; the text must have begun on an upper feature.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="description" n="letters">
            <head>Description of Letters</head>
            <p>Standard third century forms, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.025-0.03</measure>. Ligature: <foreign lang="grc">ΝΗ</foreign> (l.5). There are apices over initial aspirated vowels, including the initial <foreign lang="grc">Α</foreign> of <foreign lang="grc">ἁπάσης</foreign> (l. 9).</p>
         </div>
         <div type="description" n="date">
            <head>Date</head>
            <p><date notAfter="0267" exact="none" notBefore="0234">Mid third century</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">titulature</rs>, <rs type="criteria">language</rs>).</p>
         </div>
         <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
            <head lang="en">Edition</head>
            <ab>
              <lb n="0"/><supplied cert="low" reason="lost"><w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">δῆμος</w></supplied>
			  <lb n="1"/><persName reg="Πόπλοις Αἴλιος Σεπτίμιος Μάννος" key="Mannus" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Πόπλιος">Πόπλιον</name> <name reg="Αἴλιος">Αἴλιον</name>
			  <lb n="2"/><name reg="Σεπτίμιος">Σεπτίμιον</name>
			  <lb n="3"/><name reg="Μάννος">Μάννον</name></persName> <g type="stop"/> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w>
			  <lb n="4"/><w lemma="λαμπρός"><rs type="dignity" key="clarissimus">λαμπρότατο<hi rend="ligature" id="lig1.1">ν</hi></rs></w> <rs key="conspraes" type="official-secul"><w lemma="ἡγεμών"><hi rend="ligature" id="lig1.2">ἡ</hi><lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>γεμόνα</w></rs><link targets="lig1.1 lig1.2" targOrder="U"/> <w lemma="ὑπατικός"><hi rend="apex">ὑ</hi>πατι<lb n="6" type="worddiv"/>κόν</w><g type="stop"/> <w lemma="ἔνδοξος"><rs type="dignity" key="endoxos">ἔνδοξον</rs></w>
			  <lb n="7"/><w lemma="ἀνδρεῖος">ἀνδρεῖον</w> <w lemma="ἁγνός"><hi rend="apex">ἁ</hi>γνὸν</w>
			  <lb n="8"/><w lemma="φιλάνθρωπος">φιλάνθρωπον</w><g type="stop"/> <w lemma="διά">δι'</w>
			  <lb n="9"/><w lemma="πᾶς"><hi rend="apex">ἁ</hi>πάσης</w> <w lemma="ἥκω">ἥκοντα</w>
			  <lb n="10"/><w lemma="ἀρετή">ἀρετῆς</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w lemma="ἑαυτός"><hi rend="apex">ἑ</hi>αυ<lb n="11" type="worddiv"/>τοῦ</w> <w lemma="εὐεργέτης">εὐεργέτη<supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied></w>
              <lb n="12"/><gap dim="bottom" extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="line"/>
            </ab>
         </div>

         <div type="translation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <ab><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so honoured</supplied> Publius Aelius Septimius Mannus, the <term lang="la">clarissimus</term>, governor (<term lang="la">praeses</term>), consular, distinguished, brave, pure, generous, having achieved all virtue, his/its benefactor <gap dim="bottom" extent="unknown" reason="lost"/></ab>
         </div>

         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>The honouring body was a single masculine entity; while this could have been a grateful individual, it is perhaps more likely that such an important text was put up by the demos.</p>

            <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="I.15">I.15</xref>.</p>
            
         </div>

         <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="Basilica">Basilica</rs>: Loose find in a field wall west of Basilica.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Museum.</rs>. </p></div>

         

         

